      "content": "Entanglement isn't exactly a quirk of the universe, but rather a fundamental property of quantum mechanics. It's more like a consequence of the way particles interact with each other at a subatomic level. Think of entanglement like a game of \"linked marbles\" - imagine two marbles connected by a spring, where when one marble is pushed, the other marble is instantly pushed in the same direction, even if they're separated by a long distance. This is similar to what happens in entanglement, where the state of one particle \"influences\" the state of the other, but it's not a physical connection between them.",
